I would have also appreciated more discussion around the racial make-up of the various school/district staff--knowing the schools/districts serve a diversity of students, it was curious that the staff's racial demographics were not mentioned either, and the ways in which that could reflect larger systemic issues that need to be addressed. Lastly, I am wondering about how Dr. Price built capacity of her staff--at times, it sounded like she not only initiated the work, but that staff fell in line with her vision rather than creating a vision together.
